<br>
Leveling in PVP is kind of like the Rathe set on &quot;Hard&quot; setting. You have to kill mobs while avoiding the opposite teams. Exp is sometimes slow. For instance, fans of OT: this is a 90% &quot;dark&quot; controlled zone and any lighty caught in there is attacked on sight. Sometimes you meet X-teamers (people who will make friends with any race just to get ahead in life) and they will exp with you. Sometimes you partner up with what you think is an X-teamer just to find out when the hunting is over, he turns on you at a bad time and PKs you for your plat. Paludal is a nice blend of every race hunting there. Sometimes you have to avoid the sneaky bastards that are only out to slay you when you are low on HPs. And the occasional high level prick who trains a billion Patog fiends to you and FD then /Q to avoid tells.<br>
<br>
If you try it out, I can have my Druid keep you thorned/healed and safe while you level. Its frowned upon but so is everything else I do on this server LOL. (<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>O</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->ut <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>O</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->f <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>R</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->ange healer)<br>
